  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then the same night, I met that Ukrainian that survived from the-- from the train, who-- and he told me about a distraction.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We couldn't-- we didn't believe that things happened, what happened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even if they wrote in the papers-- first of all, the Russian paper didn't stress it too much.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and we-- in Russia, you don't trust the official news because everything is propaganda.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we thought maybe they exaggerated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that told me, if I would have met him a day before, maybe I would still stay until the end of the war in Russia because my boss told me, now you'll get papers.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you'll be free until the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from our organization, they didn't take to the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was-- since this was a important industry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But anyhow, I applied to go through the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It took us three months until we arrived to-- the headquarters of the army was in [NON-ENGLISH] By the time we came to [NON-ENGLISH], it was already in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, Lublin was--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we came to Lublin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there I met Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- I just walked away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I became a refugee from the camps-- who came from the camps and-- When did you find out-- or what did you find out about what happened in Lutsk?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That all the Jews were destroyed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because when he left, he didn't see survivors because they mobilized him a little while after he came-- later on came maybe like-- I mentioned my partner, I did-- that later on, people who survived came from little villages or from the forest, partisan.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
